longBusinessSummary: Bank of India Limited offers a wide range of banking products and services both in India and internationally. It operates through three main segments: Treasury, Wholesale Banking, and Retail Banking. The company accepts various deposit products, including savings, salary, current, and Group Personal Accident deposits. It also provides debit, credit, and prepaid cards, along with services such as Star Rewards, Green Pin, Service Charges, and Lounge Access. The bank offers loan products, including personal, home, vehicle, education, loans against property, star reverse mortgage, and approved home projects loans. In addition, the company offers financing services for new and existing businesses, healthcare schemes, government-sponsored schemes, and commercial vehicle finance services. Further, it provides credit, cash management, and trade finance services. It provides government deposit schemes, including PPF, SCSS, Sukanya Samridhi, pension, and departmentalized ministries accounts, as well as NPS, sovereign gold, RBI bonds, MSSC, and other products. Bank of India Limited also offers mutual funds and insurance services, such as life, health, and general insurance products. The bank provides NRI services, including loans, money remittance, and ancillary services. Additionally, the company provides agricultural products like the Kisan credit card, gold loan, self-help group, Atmanirbhar schemes, tractor/farm mechanization, food and agro loans, agri-allied activities, Kisan Ghar and agri-mortgage loans, agri-clinic/agri business centers, and other loan services. It also offers internet banking and online payment services. Bank of India Limited was incorporated in 1906 and is headquartered in Mumbai, India.
